<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<book xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="hcsb.xsd" id="bk.32">
    <bookname>Jonah</bookname>
    <chapter id="jonah.1" display="1">
        <head1>Jonah&#8217;s Flight</head1>
        <p type="noind">
            <verse reference="jonah.1.1" display-number="1"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.1">1</sup> The word of the <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> came to Jonah son of Amittai:<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:1"
                       data-content="2Kg 14:25; Jnh 3:1; Mt 12:39-41; 16:4; Lk 11:29-30,32">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.2" display-number="2"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.2">2</sup> &#8220;Get up!<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:2" data-content="Nm 22:20; Dt 10:11; Jos 7:10"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                Go to the great city<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:2" data-content="Jnh 3:2-3; 4:11"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                of Nineveh<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:2"
                       data-content="Gn 10:11; 2Kg 19:36; Is 37:37; Nah 1:1; Zph 2:13">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                and preach against it<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:2" data-content="Dt 15:9; 24:15; 2Kg 23:17; Is 58:1"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                because their evil<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:2" data-content="Jnh 3:8"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                has come up before me.&#8221;<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:2" data-content="Gn 18:20; Hs 7:2"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.3" display-number="3"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.3">3</sup> Jonah got up to
                flee to Tarshish<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:3" data-content="Is 23:1,6,10; Jr 10:9"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                from the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>&#8217;s presence.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:3" data-content="Gn 4:16; Ps 139:7,9-10"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                He went down<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:3" data-content="Jnh 2:6"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                to Joppa<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:3" data-content="2Ch 2:16; Ezr 3:7; Ac 9:36,43"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and found a ship going to Tarshish. He paid the fare and went down into it to go with them to Tarshish
                from the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>&#8217;s presence.
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.4" display-number="4"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.4">4</sup> But the <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> threw<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:4"
                       data-content="1Sm 18:11; 20:33; Is 22:17; Jr 22:26-28">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                a great wind onto the sea,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:4" data-content="Ps 107:25-28; 135:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and such a great storm arose on the sea that the ship threatened to break apart.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.5" display-number="5"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.5">5</sup> The sailors
                were afraid, and each cried out to his god.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:5" data-content="1Kg 18:26"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                They threw the ship&#8217;s cargo into the sea to lighten the load.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:5" data-content="Ac 27:18-19,38"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                Meanwhile, Jonah had gone down to the lowest part of the vessel and had stretched out and fallen into a
                deep sleep.<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:5"
                       data-content="Gn 2:21; 15:12; Jdg 4:21; Dn 8:18; 10:9; 1Th 5:6">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.6" display-number="6"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.6">6</sup> The captain
                approached him and said, &#8220;What are you doing sound asleep? Get up! Call to your god.
                <sup class="translate-note">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:6" data-content=" Or 'God'">
                        <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup><sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:6" data-content="Ps 107:28"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                Maybe this god will consider us,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:6" data-content="2Sm 12:22; Am 5:15; Jnh 3:9"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and we won&#8217;t perish.&#8221;
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.7" display-number="7"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.7">7</sup> &#8220;Come on!&#8201;&#8221;
                the sailors said to each other. &#8220;Let&#8217;s cast lots.<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:7"
                       data-content="Jos 7:14-18; 1Sm 10:20-21; 14:41-42; Pr 16:33; Ac 1:23-26">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                Then we&#8217;ll know who is to blame for this trouble we&#8217;re in.&#8221; So they cast lots, and the
                lot singled out Jonah.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:7" data-content="Nm 32:23; Pr 16:33"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.8" display-number="8"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.8">8</sup> Then they said
                to him, &#8220;Tell us who is to blame for this trouble we&#8217;re in.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:8" data-content="Jos 7:19; 1Sm 14:43"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                What is your business,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:8" data-content="Gn 47:3; 1Sm 30:13"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and where are you from? What is your country, and what people are you from?&#8201;&#8221;
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.9" display-number="9"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.9">9</sup> He answered
                them, &#8220;I&#8217;m a Hebrew.<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:9"
                       data-content="Gn 14:13; 39:14; Ex 1:15; 2:13; 1Sm 4:6">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                I worship
                <sup class="translate-note">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:9" data-content=" Or 'fear'">
                        <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:9" data-content="2Kg 17:25,28,32-33"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                the God of the heavens,<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:9"
                       data-content="Gn 24:3,7; Ezr 1:2; Neh 1:4; Ps 136:26; Dn 2:18">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                who made the sea<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:9" data-content="Neh 9:6; Ps 95:5; 146:6"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and the dry land.&#8221;
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.10" display-number="10"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.10">10</sup> Then the
                men were seized by a great fear and said to him, &#8220;What have you done?&#8201;&#8221;
                The men knew he was fleeing from the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>&#8217;s presence<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:10" data-content="Jnh 1:3"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                because he had told them.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.11" display-number="11"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.11">11</sup> So they
                said to him, &#8220;What should we do to you so that the sea will calm down for us?&#8201;&#8221; For
                the sea was getting worse and worse.
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.12" display-number="12"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.12">12</sup> He answered
                them, &#8220;Pick me up and throw me into the sea so that it will calm down for you, for I know that I&#8217;m
                to blame<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:12" data-content="2Sm 24:17; 1Ch 21:17"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                for this great storm that is against you.&#8221;
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.13" display-number="13"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.13">13</sup>
                Nevertheless, the men rowed hard to get back to dry land, but they couldn&#8217;t because the sea was
                raging against them more and more.
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.14" display-number="14"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.14">14</sup> So they
                called out to the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:14" data-content="Ps 107:28"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup> &#8220;Please, <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>, don&#8217;t let us perish because of this man&#8217;s
                life, and don&#8217;t charge us with innocent blood! For you, <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>, have
                done just as you pleased.&#8221;<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:14"
                       data-content="Ps 51:18; 115:3; 135:6; Pr 21:1; Is 55:11; Lm 3:37-39; Dn 4:34-35; Mt 11:25">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.15" display-number="15"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.15">15</sup> Then they
                picked up Jonah and threw him into the sea, and the sea stopped its raging.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:15" data-content="Ps 65:7; 93:3-4; 107:29"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.16" display-number="16"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.16">16</sup> The men
                were seized by great fear of the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>,<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:16"
                       data-content="Is 59:19; Mc 7:17; Zph 2:11; Mal 1:14; Lk 8:22-25">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                and they offered a sacrifice to the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span> and made vows.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:16" data-content="Ps 50:14; 66:13-14; 76:11; 116:17-18"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.1.17" display-number="17"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.1.17">17</sup> The <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> appointed a great fish<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:17" data-content="Gn 9:2; Nm 11:22; 1Kg 4:33; Ps 8:8"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                to swallow Jonah, and Jonah was in the belly of the fish three days and three nights.<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="1:17"
                       data-content="Mt 12:40; 16:4; Lk 11:29-30; Jn 11:6,14">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
    </chapter>
    <chapter id="jonah.2" display="2">
        <head1>Jonah&#8217;s Prayer</head1>
        <p type="noind">
            <verse reference="jonah.2.1" display-number="1"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.1">1</sup> Jonah prayed to
                the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span> his God from the belly of the fish:<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:1" data-content="Jb 13:15; Ps 130:1-2; Lm 3:53-56"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
        <poetryblock>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.2" display-number="2">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.2">2</sup> I called to the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span> in my distress,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:2" data-content="1Sm 30:6; Ps 18:4-6; 22:24; 120:1"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>and he answered me.</poem>
                <poem>I cried out for help from deep inside
                    <sup class="translate-note">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:2" data-content=" Lit 'from the stomach of'">
                            <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup> Sheol;<sup class="cross-ref">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:2"
                           data-content="Ps 18:5-6; 86:13; 88:1-7; Is 28:15; 38:18">
                            <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>you heard my voice.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:2" data-content="Ps 34:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.3" display-number="3">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.3">3</sup> When you threw me into the depths,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:3" data-content="Ps 69:1-2,14-15; Lm 3:54"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>into the heart of the seas,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:3" data-content="Neh 9:11"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>the current
                    <sup class="translate-note">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:3" data-content=" Lit 'river'">
                            <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                    overcame me.
                </poem>
                <poem>All your breakers and your billows swept over me.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:3" data-content="Ps 42:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.4" display-number="4">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.4">4</sup> And I said, &#8220;I have been banished<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:4" data-content="Lv 21:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>from your sight,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:4" data-content="Ps 31:22-23; Jr 7:15"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>yet I will look
                <sup class="alt-reading-note">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:4"
                           data-content=" LXX reads 'sight. Will I look . . . ?'">
                            <i class="alt-reading-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                </sup>
                 once more  
                </poem>
                <poem>toward your holy temple.&#8221;<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:4" data-content="1Kg 8:38; 2Ch 6:38; Ps 5:7; 138:2"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.5" display-number="5">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.5">5</sup> The water engulfed me up to the neck;
                    <sup class="translate-note">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:5" data-content=" Or 'me, threatening my life'">
                            <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup><sup class="cross-ref">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:5"
                           data-content="Ps 69:1-2; 105:18; Pr 23:2; Lm 3:54">
                            <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>the watery depths overcame me;</poem>
                <poem>seaweed was wrapped around my head.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:5" data-content="Ps 18:4-5"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.6" display-number="6">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.6">6</sup> I sank to the foundations of the mountains,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:6" data-content="Ps 116:3"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>the earth&#8217;s gates shut behind me forever!<sup class="cross-ref">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:6"
                           data-content="Jb 38:10; Ps 9:13; Is 38:10; Mt 16:18">
                            <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>Then you raised my life<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:6" data-content="Jb 33:28; Ps 16:10; 30:3; Is 38:17"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                    from the Pit, <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span> my God!<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:6" data-content="Ps 30:3; 86:13"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.7" display-number="7">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.7">7</sup> As my life was fading away,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:7" data-content="Ps 142:3"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>I remembered the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:7" data-content="2Sm 14:11; Ps 77:10-11; 143:5"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>and my prayer came to you,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:7" data-content="2Ch 30:27; Ps 18:6"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>to your holy temple.<sup class="cross-ref">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:7"
                           data-content="Ps 11:4; 65:4; 88:2; Mc 1:2; Hab 2:20">
                            <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.8" display-number="8">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.8">8</sup> Those who cherish worthless idols<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:8" data-content="2Kg 17:15; Ps 31:6; Jr 16:18"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>abandon their faithful love,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:8" data-content="Ps 31:6"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.9" display-number="9">
                <poem><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.9">9</sup> but as for me, I will sacrifice<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:9" data-content="Ps 50:14,23; Jr 33:11; Hs 14:2"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                    to you
                </poem>
                <poem>with a voice of thanksgiving.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:9" data-content="Ps 26:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
                <poem>I will fulfill<sup class="cross-ref">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:9"
                           data-content="Jb 22:27; Ps 22:25; 116:14,18; Ec 5:4-5">
                            <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                    what I have vowed.
                </poem>
                <poem>Salvation
                    <sup class="translate-note">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:9" data-content=" Or 'Deliverance'">
                            <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                    belongs to the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:9" data-content="Ps 3:8; Is 12:2; 45:17; Rv 7:10"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </poem>
            </verse>
        </poetryblock>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.2.10" display-number="10"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.2.10">10</sup> Then the <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> commanded the fish,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="2:10" data-content="Jnh 1:17"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and it vomited Jonah onto dry land.
            </verse>
        </p>
    </chapter>
    <chapter id="jonah.3" display="3">
        <head1>Jonah&#8217;s Preaching</head1>
        <p type="noind">
            <verse reference="jonah.3.1" display-number="1"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.1">1</sup> The word of the <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> came to Jonah a second time:<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:1" data-content="Jnh 1:1"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.2" display-number="2"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.2">2</sup> &#8220;Get up!
                Go to the great city of Nineveh<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:2" data-content="Zph 2:13-15"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and preach<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:2" data-content="Jr 1:17; Ezk 2:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                the message that I tell you.&#8221;
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.3" display-number="3"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.3">3</sup> Jonah got up
                and went to Nineveh according to the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>&#8217;s command.
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.3" display-number="3">
            Now Nineveh was an extremely great city,
            <sup class="translate-note">
                <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:3" data-content=" Or 'was a great city to God'">
                    <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                </a>
            </sup><sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:3" data-content="Gn 10:11-12; Jnh 1:2; 4:11"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            a three-day walk.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.4" display-number="4"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.4">4</sup> Jonah set out
                on the first day of his walk in the city and proclaimed,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:4" data-content="2Kg 18:26-28; Mt 12:41; Lk 11:32"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup> &#8220;In forty days Nineveh will be demolished!&#8201;&#8221;
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.5" display-number="5"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.5">5</sup> Then the people
                of Nineveh believed God. They proclaimed a fast<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:5" data-content="Dn 9:3; Jl 1:14"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                and dressed in sackcloth&#8201;&#x200B;&#8212;&#8201;&#x200B;from the greatest of them to the least.
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.6" display-number="6"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.6">6</sup> When word
                reached the king of Nineveh, he got up from his throne, took off his royal robe, covered himself with sackcloth,<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:6"
                       data-content="1Kg 21:27; Est 4:1-4; Jr 6:26; Ezk 27:30-31">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                and sat in ashes.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.7" display-number="7"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.7">7</sup> Then he issued
                a decree<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:7" data-content="2Ch 20:3; Ezr 8:21"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                in Nineveh:
            </verse>
        </p>
        <blockindent>
            <p>
                <verse reference="jonah.3.7" display-number="7">
                By order of the king and his nobles: No person or animal, herd or flock, is to taste anything at all.
                They must not eat or drink water.
                </verse>
                <verse reference="jonah.3.8" display-number="8"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.8">8</sup>
                    Furthermore, both people and animals must be covered with sackcloth, and everyone must call out
                    earnestly to God.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:8" data-content="Ps 130:1; Jnh 1:6,14"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                    Each must turn from his evil ways<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:8" data-content="Is 1:16-19; 55:6-7; Jr 18:11"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                    and from his wrongdoing.
                    <sup class="translate-note">
                        <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:8" data-content=" Or 'injustice', or 'violence'">
                            <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                        </a>
                    </sup>
                </verse>
                <verse reference="jonah.3.9" display-number="9"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.9">9</sup> Who knows?<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:9" data-content="2Sm 12:22; Jl 2:14"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                    God may turn and relent; he may turn from his burning anger so that we will not perish.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:9" data-content="Jr 18:7-8"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                </verse>
            </p>
        </blockindent>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.3.10" display-number="10"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.3.10">10</sup> God saw
                their actions&#8201;&#x200B;&#8212;&#8201;&#x200B;that they had turned from their evil ways<sup class="cross-ref">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:10"
                       data-content="1Kg 21:27-29; 2Kg 17:13; 2Ch 7:14; Jr 18:11; 31:18">
                        <i class="cross-ref-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>&#8201;&#x200B;&#8212;&#8201;&#x200B;so God relented from the disaster<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="3:10" data-content="Ex 32:14; Am 7:3,6"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                he had threatened them with. And he did not do it.
            </verse>
        </p>
    </chapter>
    <chapter id="jonah.4" display="4">
        <head1>Jonah&#8217;s Anger</head1>
        <p type="noind">
            <verse reference="jonah.4.1" display-number="1"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.1">1</sup> Jonah was
                greatly displeased and became furious.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:1" data-content="Jnh 4:9; Mt 20:15; Lk 15:28"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.2" display-number="2"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.2">2</sup> He prayed to
                the <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:2" data-content="Jr 20:7"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup> &#8220;Please, <span class="smallcaps">Lord</span>, isn&#8217;t this what I said while I was
                still in my own country? That&#8217;s why I fled toward Tarshish in the first place.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:2" data-content="Jnh 1:3"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                I knew that you are a gracious and compassionate God,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:2" data-content="Ex 34:6; Nm 14:18; Ps 86:5,15; Jl 2:13"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                slow to anger, abounding in faithful love, and one who relents from sending disaster.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:2" data-content="Neh 9:17"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.3" display-number="3"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.3">3</sup> And now, <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord</span>, take my life from me,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:3" data-content="1Kg 19:4; Jb 6:8-9"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                for it is better for me to die than to live.&#8221;<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:3" data-content="Jb 7:15-16; Ec 7:1"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.4" display-number="4"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.4">4</sup> The <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> asked, &#8220;Is it right for you to be angry?&#8201;&#8221;
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.5" display-number="5"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.5">5</sup> Jonah left the
                city and found a place east of it.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:5" data-content="1Kg 19:9,13"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                He made himself a shelter there and sat in its shade to see what would happen to the city.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.6" display-number="6"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.6">6</sup> Then the <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> God appointed a plant, and it grew over Jonah to provide shade for his head to rescue him from his
                trouble.
                <sup class="translate-note">
                    <a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:6" data-content=" Or 'disaster', or 'evil'">
                        <i class="translate-note-icon"></i>
                    </a>
                </sup>
                Jonah was greatly pleased with the plant.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.7" display-number="7"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.7">7</sup> When dawn came
                the next day, God appointed a worm that attacked the plant, and it withered.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:7" data-content="Jl 1:12"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.8" display-number="8"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.8">8</sup> As the sun was
                rising, God appointed a scorching east wind.<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:8" data-content="Ezk 19:12; Hs 13:15"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                The sun beat down on Jonah&#8217;s head<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:8" data-content="Ps 121:6; Is 49:10"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                so much that he almost fainted, and he wanted to die. He said, &#8220;It&#8217;s better for me to die
                than to live.&#8221;<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:8" data-content="Jnh 4:3"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.9" display-number="9"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.9">9</sup> Then God asked
                Jonah, &#8220;Is it right for you to be angry about the plant?&#8201;&#8221;
            </verse>
        </p>
        <verse reference="jonah.4.9" display-number="9">
        <p>&#8220;Yes, it&#8217;s right!&#8201;&#8221; he replied. &#8220;I&#8217;m angry enough to die!&#8201;&#8221;
        </p>
        </verse>
        <p>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.10" display-number="10"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.10">10</sup> And the <span
                    class="smallcaps">Lord
            </span> said, &#8220;You cared about the plant, which you did not labor over and did not grow. It appeared
                in a night and perished in a night.
            </verse>
            <verse reference="jonah.4.11" display-number="11"><sup class="verse-ref" id="jonah.4.11">11</sup> So may I
                not care about the great city of Nineveh,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:11" data-content="Jnh 3:10"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                which has more than a hundred twenty thousand people who cannot distinguish between their right and
                their left,<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:11" data-content="Dt 1:39; Is 7:16"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
                as well as many animals?&#8201;&#8221;<sup class="cross-ref"><a href="#" data-toggle="popover" title="4:11" data-content="Ps 36:6"><i class="cross-ref-icon"></i></a></sup>
            </verse>
        </p>
    </chapter>
